{"Title": "Establishing Core Cardiovascular Outcome Measures for Trials in Hemodialysis: Report of an International Consensus Workshop", "Year": 2020, "Source": "Am. J. Kidney Dis.", "Volume": "76", "Issue": 1, "Art.No": null, "PageStart": 109, "PageEnd": 120, "CitedBy": 2, "DOI": "10.1053/j.ajkd.2020.01.022", "Link": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=85089527247&origin=inward", "Abstract": "\u00a9 2020 National Kidney Foundation, Inc.Cardiovascular disease (CVD) affects more than two-thirds of patients receiving hemodialysis and is the leading cause of death in this population, yet CVD outcomes are infrequently and inconsistently reported in trials in patients receiving hemodialysis. As part of the Standardised Outcomes in Nephrology-Haemodialysis (SONG-HD) initiative, we convened a consensus workshop to discuss the potential use of myocardial infarction and sudden cardiac death as core outcome measures for CVD for use in all trials in people receiving hemodialysis. Eight patients or caregivers and 46 health professionals from 15 countries discussed selection and implementation of the proposed core outcome measures. Five main themes were identified: capturing specific relevance to the hemodialysis population (acknowledging prevalence, risk, severity, unique symptomology, and pathophysiology), the dilemmas in using composite outcomes, addressing challenges in outcome definitions (establishing a common definition and addressing uncertainty in the utility of biomarkers in hemodialysis), selecting a meaningful metric for decision making (to facilitate comparison across trials), and enabling and incentivizing implementation (by ensuring that cardiologists are involved in the development and integration of the outcome measure into registries, trial design, and reporting guidelines). Based on these themes, participants supported the use of myocardial infarction and sudden cardiac death as core outcome measures of CVD to be reported in all hemodialysis trials.", "AuthorKeywords": ["cardiovascular disease (CVD)", "core outcome set", "end-stage renal disease (ESRD)", "heart failure (HF)", "Hemodialysis (HD)", "myocardial infarction (MI)", "outcomes", "outcomes research", "patient-centered outcome (PRO)", "sudden cardiac death (SCD)", "trial design"], "IndexKeywords": ["Cardiovascular Diseases", "Clinical Trials as Topic", "Consensus", "Education", "Health Personnel", "Humans", "Internationality", "Outcome Assessment, Health Care", "Patient Participation", "Renal Dialysis", "Societies, Medical"], "DocumentType": "Journal", "PublicationStage": null, "OpenAccess": 0, "EID": "2-s2.0-85089527247", "SubjectAreas": [["Nephrology", "MEDI", "2727"]], "AuthorData": {"26039427800": {"Name": "O'Lone E.", "AuthorID": "26039427800", "AffiliationID": null, "AffiliationName": null}, "23020354400": {"Name": "Tong A.", "AuthorID": "23020354400", "AffiliationID": null, "AffiliationName": null}, "57202561844": {"Name": "Strippoli G.", "AuthorID": "57202561844", "AffiliationID": null, "AffiliationName": null}, "38362587800": {"Name": "Viecelli A.K.", "AuthorID": "38362587800", "AffiliationID": null, "AffiliationName": null}, "7401926037": {"Name": "Craig J.C.", "AuthorID": "7401926037", "AffiliationID": null, "AffiliationName": null}, "36635057700": {"Name": "Sautenet B.", "AuthorID": "36635057700", "AffiliationID": "60000905", "AffiliationName": "INSERM U1246"}, "57204947687": {"Name": "Herrington W.G.", "AuthorID": "57204947687", "AffiliationID": null, "AffiliationName": null}, "57203050475": {"Name": "Herzog C.A.", "AuthorID": "57203050475", "AffiliationID": "60019146", "AffiliationName": "Division of Cardiology, Department of Medicine, Hennepin County Medical Center/University of Minnesota"}, "6603889430": {"Name": "Jafar T.H.", "AuthorID": "6603889430", "AffiliationID": "60052016, 60067302", "AffiliationName": "Section of Nephrology, Department of Medicine, Aga Khan University"}, "22234130500": {"Name": "Jardine M.", "Au